# 🌍 TourVista – Tour Management System

TourVista is a full-stack **Django-based Tour Management System** designed to simplify travel planning and booking. It allows users to explore tour packages, make bookings, and manage their travel experience efficiently through a modern web interface.

This project demonstrates practical implementation of web development concepts including authentication, database management, and dynamic UI rendering.

---

## 🚀 Features

* 🔐 User Authentication (Register/Login/Logout)
* 🧳 Browse Travel Packages
* 📅 Book & Manage Tours
* 💳 Payment Interface (UI-based)
* 📊 Admin Dashboard
* 🗂️ Organized Tour Categories & Features
* 🧾 Booking History & Receipt Generation

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

**Frontend**

* HTML5
* CSS3
* JavaScript

**Backend**

* Python
* Django Framework

**Database**

* SQLite

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
TourVista/
│
├── accounts/        # User authentication & profiles
├── bookings/        # Booking logic and management
├── core/            # Main app (home, about, etc.)
├── features/        # Additional functionalities
├── templates/       # HTML templates
├── static/          # CSS, JS, images
├── media/           # Uploaded files
├── manage.py
└── requirements.txt
```

---

## ⚙️ Installation & Setup

### 1. Clone the repository

```
git clone https://github.com/sbraichu63/TourVista.git
cd TourVista
```

### 2. Create virtual environment

```
python -m venv venv
```

### 3. Activate virtual environment

```
# Windows
venv\Scripts\activate

# Mac/Linux
source venv/bin/activate
```

### 4. Install dependencies

```
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 5. Run migrations

```
python manage.py migrate
```

### 6. Start server

```
python manage.py runserver
```

### 7. Open in browser

```
http://127.0.0.1:8000/
```

